people at Hilton.

00:36:58.620 --> 00:37:00.290
They're not stupid.

00:37:00.290 --> 00:37:03.170
Failures are caused by--
he did research with,

00:37:03.170 --> 00:37:05.650
I think over 50 companies,
maybe more-- failures

00:37:05.650 --> 00:37:08.710
are caused by flawed executive
mindsets that throw off

00:37:08.710 --> 00:37:12.320
a company's
perception of reality,

00:37:12.320 --> 00:37:15.260
and delusional attitudes that
keep this inaccurate reality

00:37:15.260 --> 00:37:17.620
in place.

00:37:17.620 --> 00:37:19.280
We can summarize
that by being right.

00:37:22.380 --> 00:37:24.150
I did a talk, a
workshop, recently,

00:37:24.150 --> 00:37:27.680
with a very large company
in Silicon Valley.

00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:30.340
And we went through all the chat
about breakthrough innovation,

00:37:30.340 --> 00:37:31.798
it's not going to
be easy, it's not

00:37:31.798 --> 00:37:33.370
going to be pretty
a lot of the time.

00:37:33.370 --> 00:37:35.250
But we're going to get
out some big stuff.

00:37:35.250 --> 00:37:38.410
And the most senior guy who ran
the business unit-- top five

00:37:38.410 --> 00:37:41.010
in the company-- came
into the workshop

00:37:41.010 --> 00:37:44.431
and was right about everything.

00:37:44.431 --> 00:37:44.930
All that.

00:37:44.930 --> 00:37:47.420
You could see the lights
on in the senior execs--

00:37:47.420 --> 00:37:49.070
it was SVPs I was working with.

00:37:49.070 --> 00:37:50.510
The lights on--
here we are, I've

00:37:50.510 --> 00:37:52.176
been thinking about
this for five years,

00:37:52.176 --> 00:37:55.000
and now getting finally
to transform something.

00:37:55.000 --> 00:37:57.420
We had like 15
potentially massive ideas

00:37:57.420 --> 00:37:59.870
coming out, very early stage.

00:37:59.870 --> 00:38:00.920
The light just went out.

00:38:00.920 --> 00:38:04.810
And like, ah, I can't bring
