00:38:04.810 --> 00:38:08.120
I can't bring my full self,
my full passion to this place.

00:38:08.120 --> 00:38:09.960
Heartbreaking for me to see.

00:38:09.960 --> 00:38:14.610
So while assumption is
the mother all mistakes,

00:38:14.610 --> 00:38:16.381
insight is the mother
of all magnificence.

00:38:16.381 --> 00:38:18.506
And as people who work in
marketing, you know that.

00:38:18.506 --> 00:38:22.060
Without insight, you haven't got
a product that's going to work

00:38:22.060 --> 00:38:24.082
or a campaign that's
going to work.

00:38:24.082 --> 00:38:28.900
And often people masquerade
flawed thinking as insight.

00:38:28.900 --> 00:38:30.150
But we all have assumptions.

00:38:30.150 --> 00:38:33.660
This is my son
cooking in a soup.

00:38:33.660 --> 00:38:35.166
We were chopping all the veg.

00:38:35.166 --> 00:38:37.540
And I turned around to go to
the fridge to get something,

00:38:37.540 --> 00:38:39.660
and I came back and he'd
put all the peelings

00:38:39.660 --> 00:38:41.450
of the veg in the soup.

00:38:41.450 --> 00:38:45.060
And what do you think I said?

00:38:45.060 --> 00:38:47.110
No!

00:38:47.110 --> 00:38:48.992
That's not how you make soup.

00:38:48.992 --> 00:38:50.700
And being someone who
teaches this stuff,

00:38:50.700 --> 00:38:52.074
I was like, hold
on a minute, I'm

00:38:52.074 --> 00:38:56.090
doing the "that's not how we do
things around here" sentence.

00:38:56.090 --> 00:38:58.140
And lo and behold, that
evening, I found a recipe

00:38:58.140 --> 00:39:00.345
for vegetable peel soup.

00:39:00.345 --> 00:39:01.720
But think how many
times you shut

00:39:01.720 --> 00:39:04.720
yourself down and
other people down,

00:39:04.720 --> 00:39:07.160
because you know the right
way to do things around here.

00:39:09.870 --> 00:39:12.530
The right way to do a brief,
the right way to do marketing,

00:39:12.530 --> 00:39:17.979
the right way to
create an algorithm.

00:39:17.979 --> 00:39:19.270
Management's about being right.

00:39:19.270 --> 00:39:21.915
Management was born,
mainly in the '30s, '20s,

00:39:21.915 --> 00:39:25.220
'30s, professional management.

00:39:25.220 --> 00:39:29.520
Alfred Sloan, CEO of GM,
Sloan School of Management,

00:39:29.520 --> 00:39:32.310
you may have heard of,
who basically realized

00:39:32.310 --> 00:39:33.860
that to create
efficiency, we need

00:39:33.860 --> 00:39:35.440
people to do the same
thing, the right thing,

00:39:35.440 --> 00:39:36.648
over and over and over again.

00:39:36.648 --> 00:39:38.780
I don't want you to be
creative, you workers.

00:39:38.780 --> 00:39:43.402
Just stamp the metal in this
way, exactly in this way,

00:39:43.402 --> 00:39:44.360
and we'll be efficient.

00:39:46.982 --> 00:39:48.690
But we live in an age
of constant change,

00:39:48.690 --> 00:39:50.850
when no one has the
right also very long.

00:39:50.850 --> 00:39:53.840
No one-- not even Google's
algorithm has the right answer

00:39:53.840 --> 00:39:57.510
forever, I predict.

00:39:57.510 --> 00:39:59.670
So the question is, can
you break through yourself

00:39:59.670 --> 00:40:04.220
at your most successful moments,
like I did with my business,

00:40:04.220 --> 00:40:05.900
when I left my own
business at the peak.

00:40:05.900 --> 00:40:07.600
We'd just done six
or seven years.

00:40:07.600 --> 00:40:10.140
I was just getting people
to call us, rather than us

00:40:10.140 --> 00:40:11.890
calling them, which
in a consultant's life

00:40:11.890 --> 00:40:13.574
is like the holy grail.

00:40:13.574 --> 00:40:14.490
Like, we're in demand.

00:40:14.490 --> 00:40:16.740
We don't have to go and
do new business anymore.

00:40:16.740 --> 00:40:18.600
How awesome is that?

00:40:18.600 --> 00:40:21.780
And I left, because I
knew it wasn't right.

00:40:21.780 --> 00:40:24.890
So let's go live again.

00:40:24.890 --> 00:40:29.190
And we're going to switch
it on and shift, you

00:40:29.190 --> 00:40:31.727
from the left-hand side
to the right-hand side.

00:40:31.727 --> 00:40:33.102
And the way to do
this is, is you

00:40:33.102 --> 00:40:35.390
know about emotions
driving the whole ship.

00:40:35.390 --> 00:40:38.754
We can't start with behaviors,
we have to start with emotions.

00:40:38.754 --> 00:40:40.420
You say to yourself
over and over again,

00:40:40.420 --> 00:40:42.770
I'm going to not eat
the cookies anymore.

00:40:42.770 --> 00:40:47.324
And that night, the ice
scream comes out the freezer.

00:40:47.324 --> 00:40:48.740
Or, I'm not going
to drink anymore

00:40:48.740 --> 00:40:52.210
and then you're at festival--
oh gone on, then, have a pint.

00:40:52.210 --> 00:40:54.310
Familiar feeling, anyone?

00:40:54.310 --> 00:40:56.480
You have to get down
to the emotional level.

00:40:56.480 --> 00:40:58.270
So we're going to
reconnect the heart,

00:40:58.270 --> 00:41:00.410
then you can start with
rewiring the brain,

00:41:00.410 --> 00:41:03.270
and then you can get busy in
the world re-mixing the world.

