00:46:19.220 --> 00:46:21.270
The dharma, if you
like, the teaching,

00:46:21.270 --> 00:46:24.935
the truth of
breakthrough, is you've

00:46:24.935 --> 00:46:28.789
got to release the old
before you get the new.

00:46:28.789 --> 00:46:30.080
Release the old business model.

00:46:30.080 --> 00:46:32.540
Entertain the idea that
your algorithm will not

00:46:32.540 --> 00:46:34.480
be there forever.

00:46:34.480 --> 00:46:36.770
Or that your project,
or that your way

00:46:36.770 --> 00:46:40.010
of being in relationships,
or with your health,

00:46:40.010 --> 00:46:41.175
or whatever it is.

00:46:41.175 --> 00:46:43.555
You've got to release it
before you can receive it.

00:46:43.555 --> 00:46:46.250
There's no room otherwise.

00:46:46.250 --> 00:46:50.410
If you go to Ikea and you buy
a whole new kitchen suite,

00:46:50.410 --> 00:46:53.265
and you come back to
your flat and there's

00:46:53.265 --> 00:46:55.624
the old kitchen there,
what are you going to do?

00:46:55.624 --> 00:46:57.414
Like, oh!

00:46:57.414 --> 00:46:59.559
Can't get it in.

00:46:59.559 --> 00:47:01.600
So you've got to be able
to exist without kitchen

00:47:01.600 --> 00:47:02.360
for a couple of days.

00:47:02.360 --> 00:47:03.401
It's really inconvenient.

00:47:05.960 --> 00:47:08.340
You've got to excavate
the assumptions

00:47:08.340 --> 00:47:10.400
that your business
or your project

00:47:10.400 --> 00:47:12.785
is holding before
you can innovate.

00:47:12.785 --> 00:47:15.160
And the more you're willing
to let go of the assumptions,

00:47:15.160 --> 00:47:20.730
the assumption is, everyone
wants to have printed photos.

00:47:20.730 --> 00:47:24.350
People value printed photos.

00:47:24.350 --> 00:47:26.949
Let go of that to see
what they actually do.

00:47:26.949 --> 00:47:28.740
And you've got to break
it down in some way

00:47:28.740 --> 00:47:29.781
before you break through.

00:47:29.781 --> 00:47:31.420
Because the bottom
line is, everything

00:47:31.420 --> 00:47:33.430
will have to go into
break down before you

00:47:33.430 --> 00:47:34.537
can have a breakthrough.

00:47:34.537 --> 00:47:36.370
The question is whether
that breakdown feels

00:47:36.370 --> 00:47:40.390
like a disaster-- burnout,
depression, blah, blah, blah,

00:47:40.390 --> 00:47:44.680
or whether you guide it as you
lead yourself to breakthrough.

00:47:44.680 --> 00:47:46.150
And it can be
elegant and graceful

00:47:46.150 --> 00:47:50.010
and take a day
rather than 10 years.

00:47:50.010 --> 00:47:51.490
I know this the hard way.

00:47:51.490 --> 00:47:53.460
I spent six years
in psychotherapy,

00:47:53.460 --> 00:47:55.066
couldn't break
through my challenges.

00:47:55.066 --> 00:47:56.940
And that's why I went
on the 10 year journey.

00:47:56.940 --> 00:48:00.100
This book took me 10 years
to write, by the way.

00:48:00.100 --> 00:48:03.610
Because I wanted to know that
the science and the wisdom

00:48:03.610 --> 00:48:07.230
could integrate and that
I was on the right path.

